arguments.name: command
arguments.description: Command of which to display help.

flags.description: Displays a list of all commands.

MIN-LEVEL.description: Sets the minimum logging level to display in calls to 'SHOW'. Default is `DEBUG`.

examples.description: Sets the minimum logging level to display to `WARNING`.

MAX-LEVEL.description: Sets the maximum logging level to display in calls to 'SHOW'. Default is `CRITICAL`.

examples.description: Sets the maximum logging level to display to `INFO`.

NUM-PRINT.description: Sets the default number of log entries to display in calls to `SHOW`. Default is 15. Set to zero for no limit.

examples.description: Sets number of logs to display with the `SHOW` command to 10.
